Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel). Pop them onto
a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{},
then sprinkle on half the @smoked paprika{1/2%tsp}.

Toss to coat, then spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the middle shelf until golden, ~{25-35%mins}.
Turn halfway through.

== Cajun Crumb ==

In a #small bowl{}, mix together the @panko breadcrumbs{25%g},
@Cajun spice mix{1%tbsp} (add less if you'd prefer things milder), 
@grated hard Italian style cheese{25%g} and @olive oil{1%tsp} for the crumb.

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then set aside.

== Sea Bass ==

Lay the @sea bass fillets{2}, skin-side down, onto a lined baking tray.
Drizzle with @oil{} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Divide the Cajun crumb mix between your fillets and press down firmly.

Bake on the top shelf of the oven until the crumb is golden and the fish is
cooked through, ~{10-15%mins}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw fish.
> The fish is cooked when opaque in the middle.

== Paprika Mayo ==

While everything bakes, mix the @mayonnaise{64%g}, remaining
@smoked paprika{1/2%tsp} and @water{1%tsp} for the mayo in another small bowl.

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then set your paprika mayo aside.

== Garlic Broccoli ==

Cut the @broccoli{1} into florets (like small trees). Halve any large florets.
Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on high heat.

Once hot, add the broccoli and stir-fry for ~{2-3%mins}. Stir in the garlic,
then turn the heat down to medium and cook for ~{1%min}.

Add a splash of @water{} and immediately cover with a #lid{} or some #foil{}.
Allow to cook until the broccoli is tender, ~{4-5%mins}.

== To Serve ==

When everything is ready, serve the sea bass with the paprika potatoes and
garlic broccoli alongside.

Drizzle over some paprika mayo and serve the rest alongside for dipping.

Enjoy!